Date: 23/7/1986
Source: Codes for Species in NZ Waters
Author:
Vol / Page:
Edition:
Quote: [species name] scorpion fish .. [scientific name] -- [other name(s)] May be red scorpion fish or sea perch SCORPIONFISH The Red Scorpionfish is the `Grandfather Hapuku' of our deep coastal waters. A warty, barely-edible fellow he is often confused with the Sea Perch which he resembles. ... Sometimes known as `Cobbler' the Red Scorpionfish is slimmer and has a smaller eye than his look-alike, the Sea/Perch.
